                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I posted earlier about being disillusioned with charm, so, for some reason, I decided to go practice it naked (in game!, shame on you) to put maximum emphasis on technique (and not having twinkage and temp, etc). I borrowed a friends 50's cleric to hang around  and rez me, but I forbade the use of her for heals, buffs, etc, just for the xp rez.  I dont have a blue band yet, but since I am naked anyway I shallow them just to get some credit. (I am 24 btw, so this was against high blue, even and some yellows)
<br />

<br />
BTW, I die alot, but its slowly improving.
<br />

<br />
I went to loio and here are my findings.
<br />

<br />
1) I have a much bigger appreciation for spell haste and extended range focus effects. From the time tash hits the intended pet till the time charm hits has to beat the arrival, unless there is a better technique. 
<br />

<br />
2) Distance, if possible, is your friend it seems. I have my pet fight his mark as far away as possible for the jail break.  
<br />

<br />
3) When they say always root the mob the pet is fighting, they mean ALWAYS ROOT the mob the pet is fighting, I can get a re-charm or emergency mez on mr. Iamnowangryyoucharmedme much easier than I can on two. I can also mez or root the former pet if he is barely alive, and charm the rooted dude instead if he is in way better shape, and then charm burn.
<br />

<br />
4) Rune much? I have not bothered with a rune before, and I didnt do it last night, but I am thinking some kinda melee absorb should be perma up no matter what, and I am going to try tonight. Other than sheidling and mana regen, I dont keep any other self buffs up as of last night.
<br />

<br />
Its getting better but I still am missing some things to help make it less like cold fusion and more repeatably successful. My goal is to be able to solo naked at least well enough to know I have the technique down.
<br />

<br />
- If I am truly soloing, and the pet is fighting cons similar to him, he takes a ton of damage, and so here I have this pet at like 20% hp, but I am an ERU and have no $$$ for gob ring, so I dont know when to break charm on a beat up pet. I cant charm another till he's dead or broke, and I cant cast negative spells on him, so I feel stuck with him. He regens too slow to keep using, but I want to make sure I can burn him and get xp.  Should I just break him and go into pretend wizard mode and get another, or is there a slicker way? (Do npcs 40+ regen fast out of combat like 40+ pets do?)
<br />

<br />
One thing I tried for this is to mez the pets enemy right before the pet dies, hoping the charm will break on the almost dead pet, then I can switch thier places. Is this a strat that is used?
<br />

<br />
- Even one add seems to make the whole process way more complicated. Should I mez an add the second I think he's gonna aggro? Pehaps I should AE mez my pet, so as to mez all his enemies, then reassess.
<br />

<br />
- When the poop hits the fan. I still don't know the exact best way to deal with the HOLY CRAP scenario of pet is fighting mob, mob's buddy aggros, then charm breaks and its 3 inc. Is this time for a color pbaoe? I only keep one memmed. Sorry for being a noob, but should I color, then backup and ae mez? Maybe I should color, then re-charm? Looking for any tips, it seems the big jailbreak is the #1 problem staying alive.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for reading this, I am trying to get this right, and I appreciate any advisce greatly.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Vykon</span>
