                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Illusion DE doesn't give you hide, unfortunately.  Didn't know you could slam as an ogre, though!
<br />

<br />
Use what works, and what feels comfortable for you.  So... AE mez or color stun (you need both at that level, and will still get hit in the span that it doesn't quite cover).  Some chanters like to use stun locks to deal with breaks in close quarters; I prefer plenty of distance, but beggars can't be choosers.  Notice that you need at least one research only spell to work effectively at this level.
<br />

<br />
If your choice of pets are the same as what you are killing, then don't buff them, unless there is a significant level range, AND you can work out which ones are better.  So you can match like with like, get both down to nothing, break charm and kill both - your trick of mezzing to time the break is a good one, I must use that myself now.  If there is still a lot of HPs left on one, use mem blur to buy you time to deal with it, no point in wasting mana on more than one or two nukes.
<br />

<br />
Ideally your pet will be the toughest mob in the area, and you'll have hasted it and given it a weapon.  That rakes in a lot more experience per hour than matching like with like.  Makes it easier to tell which one is your pet, too <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
