Thanks for the tips, but I am curious about one aspect of the "keeper" pet (if there is a more common term of art, let me know). Since we dont have pet heals, he's going to gradually get worn down from tankign his opponent.
<br />

<br />
Doesnt waiting for his HP to recover due to lack of heals slow things down alot?
<br />

<br />
Am I missing a spell, technique or trick to deal with this.
<br />

<br />
I tried having a perma pet, even had a passerby hp buff them, but then they get wore down in hp, what do I do? If I burn them that goes against the keeper idea.
<br />

<br />
Is it that I am soloing wrong, vis a vis having them tank? Should it be more like a mage (I played one to 41) where my nukes are a big part of the equation, as oppopsed to the pet tanking? Even my mage had some pet heals, tho.
<br />

<br />
 I thought the idea was my pet hasted + feedbacked> their peer slowed + debuffed, then burn him when he gets low. I like the idea of the keeper pet, but I dont know how to handle his getting worn down to a nub.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for tips, I'm eating them up.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Vykon</span>
<br />
Chromedome Enchanter, Ayonae Ro</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
