                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rune, and Berzerker Strength, are the enchanter heals, pathetic though they are.  Just know your pets - find one with lots of hp and ac.  A good pet can kill 4 - 6 mobs when hasted and them slowed.  When he's low, don't kill him necessarily; you can, but it depends on the pet.  Break charm, mez and mem blur.  Some pets regen very fast; again, you need to learn which ones.
<br />

<br />
The other way round this is to find a bored druid or cleric, and have them heal for you.
<br />

<br />
Good pets are, for example and close to your level, Bloodmaw in the kodiak caves in GD - level 20, low MR, and 32K hit points; and Brell Anchorite gnolls in Jaggedpine, any one of which will kill 6-8 basilisks in a row.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
