                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You don't need to practice charming naked if you want to improve your technique.  Just equip things that don't have focus effects.
<br />

<br />
If you want to practice, just remember the following thoughts:
<br />

<br />
You only have to worry about three things when charming:  Getting the charm to land, Keeping the charm on the mob, and being able to recharm.  
<br />

<br />
As for more long-term pets, don't worry if they get worn down.  It's not like you didn't have to rebuff it and recharm it anyway so you may as well kill it.  You can just concentrate on finding and debuffing another pet while your pet gets super low and just switch when convenient.  It's not healthy keeping the same charmed pet ALL the time anyway...it cuts down on your available medding time since you don't have a lot of control over charm breaks, and the charm used for the appropriate level tends to chew into your mana pool pretty well in most cases.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sleeping for 65 nights (with 188 interruptions...)
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=467231" target="_blank" class="postlink">ZZZzzzzzz...</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
