                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For initial charms, I Mez (with level 4 Mesmerize), Tash (with Tashania), and then charm.  For unmezzables (like giants), I use Root instead of Mez.
<br />

<br />
I charm indoors -- I never hunt outdoors, lot of LDoN -- so I have gotten used to no Extended Range foci and just using Color Shift/Entrancing Lights to give me enough time to Mez, Tash, and Charm again.  Again with unmezzables, I use Root instead of Mez.
<br />

<br />
Reagent Conservation is your friend!  An RC item pays for itself eventually in saved reagents until you get Arcane Rune at 61.  Berserker Strength line will do (but not as well as Rune) if you run out of 'dots though.
<br />

<br />
I keep some form of Pacify loaded for potential adds.  Otherwise, just Mez them and deal with them later.  Too many adds, Gate or run to zone, with Color Shift or Entrancing Lights if they're beating on you.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Provender Moonshadow</a>, High Elf Phantasmist
<br />
<a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=18979" target="_blank" class="postlink">E61/TT h+ 1.5khp 3.2km ft1 G&lt;3 e+ o++ T+++ L H++ !f g+ b c+++ !t D-- !X</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
